]]'' (January 28, 2003)</ref><ref>[http://www.educacional.com.br/reportagens/cultura_paz/default.asp Cultura de Paz \u2013 virando a mesa da violencia], ''educacional.com.br'' (February 14, 2003)</ref>\n|-\n| April 14, 2003\n| [[New Orleans, Louisiana]], United States\n| Steven Williams,<br>James Tate<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20080421113821/http://nola.live.advance.net/news/t-p/metro/index.ssf?%2Fbase%2Fnews-17%2F1158829217114200.xml&coll=1 4 plead guilty in killing at school \u2013 NOLA.com]. Nola.live.advance.net (2006-09-21). Retrieved on 2010-08-16.</ref>\n| 1 dead,\n| 4 injured\n| [[2003 John McDonogh High School shooting|John McDonogh High School shooting]]. 15-year-old Jonathan Williams, a student and football player, was fatally shot while sitting on the [[bleachers]] in the gymnasium of [[New Orleans Public Schools|John McDonogh Senior High School]], by two men armed with an [[AK-47]] [[assault rifle]] and a [[handgun]]. The two gunmen fired at least 18 rounds from their weapons, shattering Williams' face, and injuring three girls.\n|-\n| April 24, 2003\n| [[Red Lion, York County, Pennsylvania|Red Lion, Pennsylvania]], United States\n| James Sheets, 14\n| 2 dead\n|\n| [[Red Lion Area Junior High School shooting]]. 14-year-old student James Sheets, armed with [[.44 Magnum|.44]] and [[.357 Magnum|.357-caliber]] [[revolver]]s and a [[.22 Long Rifle|.22-caliber]] [[pistol]], shot and killed Principal Eugene Segro and then committed suicide in the school cafeteria of Red Lion Area Junior High School, in [[Red Lion, York County, Pennsylvania|Red Lion]], [[Pennsylvania]].<ref name=\"nytimes42503\">{{cite news|title=Middle School Boy Shoots His Principal, Then Kills Himself|date=2003-04-25|url =https://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=980DEEDC173DF936A15757C0A9659C8B63|work=[[The New York Times]]|accessdate = 2009-04-25}}</ref><ref name=\"bbcnews42403\">{{cite news|first=Steve|last=Kingstone|title=Two die in US school shooting|date=2003-04-24|work=BB