ently had a list with the names of 24 people he wanted to kill. This was the first ever attack in a school by perpetrated by a student in Spain's history. The attack came to an end after the student had a breakdown when his PE teacher managed to talk to him. The student then proceeded to sit down in a classroom until the police arrived. Under Spanish law, the boy is exempt from legal responsibility because he was under 14 years old at the time. He is now in a psychiatric clinic in his locality.\n|-\n|{{Dts|April 22, 2015}}\n| [[Desert Hot Springs, California]], United States\n| Suspect, 12\n|\n| 1 injured\n| A 13-year-old student was stabbed by a 12-year-old classmate at Painted Hills Middle School. The suspect was arrested. The victim received non-life threatening injuries.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.desertsun.com/story/news/crime_courts/2015/04/23/student-stabs-classmate-at-painted-hills-middle-school/26270911/|title=Police: Boy, 12, stabs Painted Hills Middle School classmate|website=desertsun.com}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{Dts|April 27, 2015}}\n| [[Lacey, Washington]], United States\n| Suspect, 16\n|\n| No injuries\n| In the [[North Thurston High School Shooting]], a student at [[North Thurston High School]] walked into the commons area and fired two shots into the ceiling from a .357 magnum pistol. Brady Olson, a teacher at the school, was able to tackle the student before they could turn the gun on other students. No one was injured or killed.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.komonews.com/news/local/Gunman-at-North-Thurston-High-School-apprehended-by-staff-301426921.html|title=Gunman tackled by teacher after firing shots at N. Thurston H.S.|publisher=KOMO News|date=April 27, 2015|accessdate=April 27, 2015}}</ref><ref name=TribuneGun>{{cite news|title=Washington teacher who stopped shooter's first thought: Get the gun away|url=https://www.chicagotribune.com/news/nationworld/chi-washington-school-shooting-teacher-20150428-story.html|accessdate=4 June 2015|agency=Tribune wi