0\u20132001], ''National School Safety and Security Services''\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20110722181216/http://www.schoolsecurity.org/trends/school_violence02-03.html School-Related Deaths, School Shootings, & School Violence Incidents: 2002\u20132003], ''National School Safety and Security Services''\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20110722181239/http://www.schoolsecurity.org/trends/school_violence04-05.html School-Related Deaths, School Shootings, & School Violence Incidents: 2004\u20132005], ''National School Safety and Security Services''\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20110722181347/http://www.schoolsecurity.org/trends/school_violence06-07.html School-Related Deaths, School Shootings, & School Violence Incidents: 2006\u20132007], ''National School Safety and Security Services''\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20110722181441/http://www.schoolsecurity.org/trends/school_violence07-08.html School-Related Deaths, School Shootings, & School Violence Incidents: 2007\u20132008], ''National School Safety and Security Services''\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20110722181632/http://www.schoolsecurity.org/trends/school_violence08-09.html School-Related Deaths, School Shootings, & School Violence Incidents: 2008\u20132009], ''National School Safety and Security Services''\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20110722181945/http://www.schoolsecurity.org/trends/school_violence09-10.html School-Related Deaths, School Shootings, & School Violence Incidents: 2009\u20132010], ''National School Safety and Security Services''\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:School-Related Attacks}}\n[[Category:Attacks on schools|*]]\n[[Category:Lists of schools|*]]\n[[Category:Crime-related lists]]\n[[Category:Secondary education-related lists]]\n[[Category:Lists of school-related attacks|secondary]]\n", "name_user": "BorderRegions", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200e2010s", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_attacks_related_to_secondary_schools"}
{"title_page": "Cathy H. Wu", "text_new": "{{like resume |date=December 2016}}\n\n{{Infobox scientist\n| name              = Cathy H. Wu\n| image             =\n| image_size        =\n| caption           = \n| birth_date        = \n| birth_place       = \n| death_date        = \n| death_place       = \n| residence         = \n| citizenship       = \n| nationality       =\n| ethnicity         = \n| fields            = [[Computational Biology]]<br />[[Biochemistry]]<br />[[Oncology]]<br />[[Bioinformatics]]\n| workplaces        = [[University of Delaware]]<br />[[Georgetown University Medical Center]]\n| alma_mater        = \n| doctoral_advisor  = \n| academic_advisors = \n| doctoral_students = \n| notable_students  = \n| known_for         = \n| author_abbrev_bot = \n| author_abbrev_zoo = \n| influences        = \n| influenced        = \n| awards            = \n| religion          = \n| signature         =  <!--(filename only)-->\n| footnotes         = \n}}\n\n'''Cathy H. Wu''' is the Edward G. Jefferson Chair and professor and director of the Center for Bioinformatics & Computational Biology (CBCB) at the [[University of Delaware]]. She is also the director of the [[Protein Information Resource]] (PIR) and the North east Bioinformatics Collaborative Steering Committee, and the adjunct professor at the [[Georgetown University Medical Center]].<ref name=bioinformatics>{{cite web|url=http://bioinformatics.udel.edu/People/Cathy_Wu|title=Center For Bioinformatics & Computational Biology|accessdate=15 February 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Early life and education==\nWu is the middle child of the five daughters and a son in her family. She responded with top marks at [[National Taiwan University]] and showed a flair for science, logic, and computations. Her father was an [[aeronautics engineer]].<ref name=thescientist>{{cite web|url=http://www.the-scientist.com/?articles.view/articleNo/13641/title/Cathy-Wu-at-the-Crossroads/|title=Cathy Wu at the Crossroads|accessdate=15 February 2015}}</ref> She graduated with a [[Bachelor of Science|BS]] in [[Plant Pathology]] at the [[National Taiwan University]] in 1978, a [[Master of Science|MS]] in Plant Pathology at [[Purdue University]] in 1982 and followed with a  [[PhD]] in the same university in 1984. She then received a [[Postdoc]] degree in [[Molecular Biology]] at the [[Michigan State University]] in 1986 and a [[Master of Science|MS]] in [[Computer Science]] at the [[University of Texas]] (UT) at Tyler in 1989.<ref name=bioinformatics />\n\n==Career==\nIn 1989, Wu completed her thesis on the use of artificial neural networks to classify proteins, and graduated. Her thesis advisor, George M. Witson III, chairman of the Computer Science Department at [[University of Texas|UT]] hired her after she graduated in 1989. She then taught computer science as an assistant professor at the Department of Computer Science in UT Tyler from 1989 to 1994. She also worked as an assistant professor from 1990 to 1994, associate professor from 1994 to 1998, and professor from 1998 to 1999 of the Biomathematics University of Texas Health Center at Tyler. She carried out research at the UT Tyler's health sciences college under [[epidemiology]] and [[biomathematics]] professor Jerry McClarty. She has conducted [[bioinformatics]] research from 1990 and developed several protein classification systems and databases. She also managed large software and database projects leading bioinformatics effort of the Protein Information Resource (PIR) from 1999, and became the PIR Director and the vice president of the National Biomedical Research Foundation, Washington, D.C. from 2001 to 2002. From 2001 until present, she is the professor of the Department of [[Biochemistry]] & Molecular Biology and the Director of PIR [[Georgetown University Medical Center]] (GUMC). She is also currently the professor at the Department of [[Oncology]] and the member of the [[Lombardi Comprehensive Cancer Center]], GUMC from 2002. In 2009, Wu was accepted as the Edward G. Jefferson Chair of Bioinformatics and Computational Biology at the University of Delaware (UD).<ref name=bioinformatics /><ref name=georgetown>{{cite web|url=http://pir.georgetown.edu/pirwww/aboutpir/wubio.shtml|accessdate=15 February 2015|title=Protein Information Resource, Cahty H. Wu, Ph.D.}}</ref>\n\n==Awards granted==\n*'''July 2012 to June 2017''' - 1144726, NSF/DGE, IGERT: Systems Biology of Cells in Engineered Environments (SBE2). Role: Co-PI\n*'''September 2011 to August 2015''' - 2R01GM080646-06 & 3R01GM80646-07S1, NIH/NIGMS, PRO: A Protein Ontology in Open Biomedical Ontologies. Role: PI\n*'''July 2011 to June 2015''' - 1062520, NSF/DBI, ABI Development: Integrative Bioinformatics for Knowledge Discovery of PTM Networks. Role: PI\n*'''September 2011 to August 2014''' - DOE/FOA-0000368, Experimental Systems-Biology Approaches for Clostridia-Based Bioenergy Production. Role: Co-PI\n*'''November 2009 to February 2014''' - 8P20GM103446, NIH/NIGMS, Delaware INBRE Role: Bioinformatics Core Director\n*'''August 2010 to 2013''' - 1G08 LM010720-01, NIH/NLM, Linking Text Mining and Data Mining for Biomedical Knowledge Discovery. Role: PI\n*'''September 2010 to July 2013''' - 1U41HG006104-01, NIH/NHGRI, UniProt: A Centralized Protein Sequence and Function Resource. Role: Co-PI\n*'''September 2009 to August 2012''' - DBI-0850319, NSF/DBI, Linking Text Mining with Ontology and Systems Biology. Role: PI\n*'''June 2011 to May 2012''' - 1137427, NSF/IIS, III: Small: Women in Bioinformatics Initiative at ACM BCB 2011. Role: Co-PI\n*'''September 2009 to April 2012''' - 3R01GM080646-04S2, NIH/NIGMS, Pro: A Protein Ontology in Open Biomedical Ontologies. Role: PI<ref name=learnerudel>{{cite web|url=http://www.lerner.udel.edu/faculty-staff/cathy-wu|accessdate=15 February 2015|title=University of Delaware Directory, Cathy Wu, Grant Awards|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402144338/http://www.lerner.udel.edu/faculty-staff/cathy-wu#|archive-date=2015-04-02|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n==Books and publications==\n\n===Books===\n*''Bioinformatics for Comparative Proteomics (Methods in Molecular Biology),'' November 19, 2010, by Cathy H. Wu (Editor), Chuming Chen (Editor), ''{{ISBN|978-1607619765}}''\n*''Computational Biology and Genome Informatics,'' February 2003, by Cathy H. Wu (Author), Paul P. Wang (Author), Jason T. L. Wang (Editor), ''{{ISBN|978-9812382573}}''\n*''Neural Networks and Genome Informatics, Volume 1 (Methods in Computational Biology and Biochemistry),'' October 5, 2000, by C.H. Wu (Editor), J.W. McLarty (Editor), ''{{ISBN|978-0080428000}}''<ref name=bioinformatics />\n\n===Publications===\n*UniProt: a hub for protein information. UniProt Consortium. ''Nucleic Acids Res.'' Jan 28;43 (Database issue) (2015)\n*{{cite journal | last1 = Suzek | first1 = BE | last2 = Wang | first2 = Y | last3 = Huang | first3 = H | last4 = McGarvey | first4 = PB | last5 = Wu | first5 = CH | year = 2014 | title = UniRef clusters: a comprehensive and scalable alternative for improving sequence similarity searches | journal = Bioinformatics | volume = 31| issue = 6| pages = 926\u201332| doi = 10.1093/bioinformatics/btu739 | pmid = 25398609 | pmc=4375400}}\n*{{cite journal | pmid = 24270789 | doi=10.1093/nar/gkt1173 | volume=42 | title=Protein Ontology: a controlled structured network of protein entities | pmc=3964965 | year=2014 | journal=Nucleic Acids Res. | pages=D415\u201321  | last1 = Natale | first1 = DA | last2 = Arighi | first2 = CN | last3 = Blake | first3 = JA | last4 = Bult | first4 = CJ | last5 = Christie | first5 = KR | last6 = Cowart | first6 = J | last7 = D'Eustachio | first7 = P | last8 = Diehl | first8 = AD | last9 = Drabkin | first9 = HJ | last10 = Helfer | first10 = O | last11 = Huang | first11 = H | last12 = Masci | first12 = AM | last13 = Ren | first13 = J | last14 = Roberts | first14 = NV | last15 = Ross | first15 = K | last16 = Ruttenberg | first16 = A | last17 = Shamovsky | first17 = V | last18 = Smith | first18 = B | last19 = Yerramalla | first19 = MS | last20 = Zhang | first20 = J | last21 = AlJanahi | first21 = A | last22 = \u00c7elen | first22 = I | last23 = Gan | first23 = C | last24 = Lv | first24 = M | last25 = Schuster-Lezell | first25 = E | last26 = Wu | first26 = CH}}\n*{{cite journal | pmid =  24253303 | doi=10.1093/nar/gkt1140 | volume=42 | title=Activities at the Universal Protein Resource (UniProt) | pmc=3965022 | year=2014 | journal=Nucleic Acids Res. | pages=D191\u20138 }}<ref name=georgetown />\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://proteininformationresource.org/ Protein Information Resource]\n*[http://bioinformatics.udel.edu/People/Cathy_Wu Center For Bioinformatics and Computational Biology, University of Delaware]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Wu, Cathy H.}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:University of Delaware faculty]]\n[[Category:Taiwanese women scientists]]\n[[Category:American women computer scientists]]\n[[Category:Women molecular biologists]]\n[[Category:20th-century American women scientists]]\n[[Category:21st-century American women scientists]]\n[[Category:20th-century Taiwanese scientists]]\n[[Category:20th-century Taiwanese women]]\n[[Category:21st-century Taiwanese scientists]]\n[[Category:21st-century Taiwanese women]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n", "text_old": "{{like resume |date=December 2016}}\n\n{{Infobox scientist\n| name              = Cathy H. Wu\n| image             =\n| image_size        =\n| caption           = \n| birth_date        = \n| birth_place       = \n| death_date        = \n| death_place       = \n| residence         = \n| citizenship       = \n| nationality       =\n| ethnicity         = \n| fields            = [[Computational Biology]]<br />[[Biochemistry]]<br />[[Oncology]]<br />[[Bioinformatics]]\n| workplaces        = [[University of Delaware]]<br />[[Georgetown University Medical Center]]\n| alma_mater        = \n| doctoral_advisor  = \n| academic_advisors = \n| doctoral_students = \n| notable_students  = \n| known_for         = \n| author_abbrev_bot = \n| author_abbrev_zoo = \n| influences        = \n| influenced        = \n| awards            = \n| religion          = \n| signature         =  <!--(filename only)-->\n| footnotes         = \n}}\n\n'''Cathy H. Wu''' is the Edward G. Jefferson Chair and professor and director of the Center for Bioinformatics & Computational Biology (CBCB) at the [[University of Delaware]]. She is also the director of the [[Protein Information Resource]] (PIR) and the North east Bioinformatics Collaborative Steering Committee, and the adjunct professor at the [[Georgetown University Medical Center]].<ref name=bioinformatics>{{cite web|url=http://bioinformatics.udel.edu/People/Cathy_Wu|title=Center For Bioinformatics & Computational Biology|accessdate=15 February 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Early life and education==\nWu is the middle child of the five daughters and a son in her family. She responded with top marks at [[National Taiwan University]] and showed a flair for science, logic, and computations. Her father was an [[aeronautics engineer]].<ref name=thescientist>{{cite web|url=http://www.the-scientist.com/?articles.view/articleNo/13641/title/Cathy-Wu-at-the-Crossroads/|title=Cathy Wu at the Crossroads|accessdate=15 February 2015}}</ref> She graduated with a [[Bachelor of Science|BS]] in [[Plant Pathology]] at the [[National Taiwan University]] in 1978, a [[Master of Science|MS]] in Plant Pathology at [[Purdue University]] in 1982 and followed with a  [[PhD]] in the same university in 1984. She then received a [[Postdoc]] degree in [[Molecular Biology]] at the [[Michigan State University]] in 1986 and a [[Master of Science|MS]] in [[Computer Science]] at the [[University of Texas]] (UT) at Tyler in 1989.<ref name=bioinformatics />\n\n==Career==\nIn 1989, Wu completed her thesis on the use of artificial neural networks to classify proteins, and graduated. Her thesis advisor, George M. Witson III, chairman of the Computer Science Department at [[University of Texas|UT]] hired her after she graduated in 1989. She then taught computer science as an assistant professor at the Department of Computer Science in UT Tyler from 1989 to 1994. She also worked as an assistant professor from 1990 to 1994, associate professor from 1994 to 1998, and professor from 1998 to 1999 of the Biomathematics University of Texas Health Center at Tyler. She carried out research at the UT Tyler's health sciences college under [[epidemiology]] and [[biomathematics]] professor Jerry McClarty. She has conducted [[bioinformatics]] research from 1990 and developed several protein classification systems and databases. She also managed large software and database projects leading bioinformatics effort of the Protein Information Resource (PIR) from 1999, and became the PIR Director and the vice president of the National Biomedical Research Foundation, Washington, D.C. from 2001 to 2002. From 2001 until present, she is the professor of the Department of [[Biochemistry]] & Molecular Biology and the Director of PIR [[Georgetown University Medical Center]] (GUMC). She is also currently the professor at the Department of [[Oncology]] and the member of the [[Lombardi Comprehensive Cancer Center]], GUMC from 2002. In 2009, Wu was accepted as the Edward G. Jefferson Chair of Bioinformatics and Computational Biology at the University of Delaware (UD).<ref name=bioinformatics /><ref name=georgetown>{{cite web|url=http://pir.georgetown.edu/pirwww/aboutpir/wubio.shtml|accessdate=15 February 2015|title=Protein Information Resource, Cahty H. Wu, Ph.D.}}</ref>\n\n==Awards granted==\n*'''July 2012 to June 2017''' - 1144726, NSF/DGE, IGERT: Systems Biology of Cells in Engineered Environments (SBE2). Role: Co-PI\n*'''September 2011 to August 2015''' - 2R01GM080646-06 & 3R01GM80646-07S1, NIH/NIGMS, PRO: A Protein Ontology in Open Biomedical Ontologies. Role: PI\n*'''July 2011 