{"title_page": "List of tallest buildings in Myanmar", "text_new": "This is a '''list of tallest buildings''' in [[Myanmar]]. The list includes habitable buildings standing at or above 90 meters (295 feet) but excludes other structures above 90 meters such as the [[Laykyun Sekkya|Laykyun Sekkya Buddha Statue]], the [[Shwemawdaw Pagoda]], the [[Shwesandaw Pagoda (Bagan)|Shwesandaw Pagoda]], or the [[Shwedagon Pagoda]]. For other tallest structures, see [[List of tallest structures in Myanmar]].\n\nAll of Myanmar's tallest buildings are [[High-rise building|high rises]]. The country does not have a [[skyscraper]]\u2014i.e. one at least 150 meters tall as defined by the [[Council on Tall Buildings and Urban Habitat]] and [[Emporis]].<ref name=skyscraper>{{cite web | url=https://theurbandeveloper.com/articles/which-world-city-has-the-most-skyscrapers | title=Which World City Has The Most Skyscrapers?\" | publisher=The Urban Developer | date=2016-03-11 | accessdate=2020-04-11}}</ref><ref name=emporis-myanmar>{{cite web | url=https://www.emporis.com/country/100112/myanmar | title=Myanmar | publisher=Emporis | accessdate=2020-04-08}}</ref> Most of the tallest buildings are located in [[Yangon]] where zoning regulations restrict the maximum height of buildings to 127 meters (417 feet) above sea level,<ref name=yangon-height>{{cite web | last=Lau | first=Bo Yee | url=https://fac.arch.hku.hk/asian-cities-research/yangon-2007-2017-height-restriction-policies-that-shape-both-the-urban-and-economic-landscape/ | title=Yangon (2007-2017): Height Restriction Policies That Shape Both the Urban and Economic Landscape | publisher=The University of Hong Kong}}</ref><ref name=lincoln>{{cite web | url=https://www.lincolnmyanmar.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/4-August-2016-Seminar-land-law-stamp-duty.pdf | author=Lincoln Legal Services Myanmar | title=LAND LAW / STAMP DUTY IN MYANMAR | date=August 2016 | accessdate=2020-04-11}}</ref> in order to prevent buildings from overtaking the [[Shwedagon Pagoda]].<ref name=obg>{{cite web | author=Oxford Business Group| title=Striking a balance: New housing and office projects are changing the landscape of cities | url=https://oxfordbusinessgroup.com/overview/striking-balance-new-housing-and-office-projects-are-changing-landscape-cities | accessdate=2020-04-18 | year=2013}}</ref> The first ever attempt to build a skyscraper in the country\u2014a 195-meter (640-foot) tower in [[downtown Yangon]]\u2014<ref name=555-Merchant>{{cite web | url=https://www.emporis.com/buildings/1210437/555-merchant-office-tower-yangon-myanmar | title=555 Merchant Office Tower | publisher=Emporis | accessdate=2020-04-11}}</ref> faced intense opposition by local conservationists, and was cancelled in 2014.<ref name=nat-geo>{{cite journal | last=Palmer | first=Alex | url=https://www.nationalgeographic.com/news/2014/11/141112-myanmar-burma-yangon-rangoon-heritage-architecture/ | title=The Race to Save Architecture in Myanmar's Biggest City | journal=The National Geographic | date=2014-11-13}}</ref>\n\n==Tallest buildings==\nThe following list ranks completed buildings in Myanmar that stand ''about'' 90 meters (295 feet) or taller based on the estimates by Emporis, unless otherwise stated. Because of its use of Emporis's estimates, the list may not be fully accurate\u2014in terms of inclusion and rankings. (Emporis estimates the height of buildings based on the number of floors; as a result, buildings with the same number of floors\u2014regardless of the type (office or residential)\u2014are estimated at the same height.<ref group=note>See Emporis's estimates for Yangon buildings here: [https://www.emporis.com/city/101677/yangon-myanmar/status/all-buildings].</ref>) The estimated heights are given in ''italics''.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable zebra\"\n|- class=\"hintergrundfarbe6\"\n! Rank\n! Name\n! class=\"unsortable\"|Image\n! Location\n! Height: <br/>m (ft)\n! Floors\n! Year\n! Notes\n! References\n|-\n| 1\n| [[Diamond Inya Palace]]\n| \n| [[Yangon]]\n| ''{{convert|122|m|ft|0|abbr=on}}''\n| 34\n| 2019\n| \n| <ref name=emporis>{{cite web | url=https://www.emporis.com/statistics/tallest-buildings/country/100112/myanmar | title=Myanmar's tallest buildings - Top 20 | publisher=EMPORIS | accessdate=2020-04-05}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\" | 2\n| [[Golden City, Yangon|Golden City I]] \n| \n| rowspan=\"4\" | [[Yangon]]\n| rowspan=\"4\" | {{convert|109.7|m|ft|0|abbr=on}}\n| rowspan=\"4\" | 33\n| rowspan=\"4\" | 2018\n| rowspan=\"4\" | \n| rowspan=\"4\" | <ref name=dp-gc>{{cite web | url=https://www.dotproperty.com.mm/en/condo/6259/golden-city | title=Golden City | publisher=Dot Property | accessdate=2020-04-18}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Golden City, Yangon|Golden City II]]\n| \n|-\n| [[Golden City, Yangon|Golden City III]]\n| \n|-\n| [[Golden City, Yangon|Golden City IV]]\n| \n|-\n| 6\n| [[Lotte Hotel Yangon Residences]]\n| \n| [[Yangon]]\n| ''{{convert|104|m|ft|0|abbr=on}}''\n| 29\n| 2017\n| \n| <ref name=emporis/>\n|-\n| 6=\n| [[Sedona Hotel II]]\n| \n| [[Yangon]]\n| ''{{convert|104|m|ft|0|abbr=on}}''\n| 29\n| 2016\n| \n| <ref name=emporis/>\n|-\n| 8\n| [[Sakura Tower]]\n| [[File:Sakura Tower, Yangon, Myanmar.jpg|alt=|center|frameless|100px]]\n| [[Yangon]]\n| {{convert|100|m|ft|0|abbr=on}}\n| 20\n| 1999\n| \n| <ref name=sakura>{{cite web | url=http://www.sakura-tower-yangon.com/ | title=About Sakura Tower | date=2020-04-16}}</ref>\n|-\n| 9\n| [[Kaba Aye Executive Residence]]\n| \n| [[Yangon]]\n| ''{{convert|97|m|ft|0|abbr=on}}''\n| 27\n| 2016\n| \n| <ref name=emporis/>\n|-\n| 9=\n| [[Paragon Residence]]\n| \n| [[Yangon]]\n| ''{{convert|97|m|ft|0|abbr=on}}''\n| 27\n| 2018\n| \n| <ref name=emporis/>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 11\n| [[Myanmar Plaza|Myanmar Plaza I]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" | [[File:Myanmar Plaza.jpg|alt=|center|frameless|100px]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" | [[Yangon]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" | ''{{convert|97|m|ft|0|abbr=on}}''\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 27\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2015\n| rowspan=\"2\" | \n| rowspan=\"2\" | <ref name=emporis/>\n|-\n| [[Myanmar Plaza|Myanmar Plaza II]]\n|-\n| 13\n| [[Grand Park Hotel]]\n| \n| [[Mandalay]]\n| ''{{convert|93|m|ft|0|abbr=on}}''\n| 26\n| 2019\n| \n| <ref name=emporis/>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 14\n| [[Star City, Thanlyin|Star City I]] \n| \n| rowspan=\"2\" | [[Thanlyin]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" | {{convert|91|m|ft|0|abbr=on}}\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 28\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2019\n| rowspan=\"2\" | \n| rowspan=\"2\" | <ref group=note>Per the building contractor, {{cite web | url=https://www.bouygues-construction.com/en/press/release/new-project-bouygues-construction-myanmar | title=A new project for Bouygues Construction in Myanmar | accessdate=2020-04-16}}, the complex consists of two 91-meter tall 28-story towers, and four 82-meter tall 25-story buildings.</ref>\n|-\n| [[Star City, Thanlyin|Star City II]] \n| \n|-\n| 16\n| [[Pyay Garden]]\n| \n| [[Yangon]]\n| {{convert|90|m|ft|0|abbr=on}}\n| 25\n| 2013\n| \n| <ref name=sp-pg>{{cite web | url=https://skyscraperpage.com/cities/?buildingID=46904 | title=Pyay Garden Condominium | publisher=Skyscraper Page | accessdate=2020-04-16}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 16=\n| [[Centrepoint Towers|Centrepoint Office Tower]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" | [[File:Pabedan Yangon downtown IMG 20180407 131611 sule road Yangon.jpg|alt=|center|frameless|100px]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" | [[Yangon]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" | ''{{convert|90|m|ft|0|abbr=on}}''\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 25\n| 2012\n| rowspan=\"2\" | Construction began in 1995\n| rowspan=\"2\" | <ref name=emporis/>\n|-\n| [[Centrepoint Towers|Pullman Centrepoint Hotel]]\n| 2014\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 16=\n| [[Mann Myanmar Plaza|Mann Myanmar Plaza I]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" | \n| rowspan=\"2\" | [[Mandalay]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" | ''{{convert|90|m|ft|0|abbr=on}}''\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 25\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2014\n| rowspan=\"2\" | \n| rowspan=\"2\" | <ref name=emporis/>\n|-\n| [[Mann Myanmar Plaza|Mann Myanmar Plaza II]]\n|-\n| 16=\n| [[Times City, Yangon|Times City Office Tower I]]\n| \n| [[Yangon]]\n| ''{{convert|90|m|ft|